  "content": "<div style=\"background:#f0f7ff; border-left:4px solid #0066cc; padding:16px 20px; margin-bottom:24px; border-radius:4px;\"><strong style=\"font-size:15px;\">[Key Takeaways]</strong><p style=\"margin:6px 0; line-height:1.7;\">✅ Learn the fundamentals of buying shares in publicly traded companies.</p><p style=\"margin:6px 0; line-height:1.7;\">✅ Discover how diversified portfolios help mitigate market volatility in 2026.</p><p style=\"margin:6px 0; line-height:1.7;\">✅ Follow a step-by-step approach to opening your first brokerage account.</p></div><p>Have you ever looked at a company like Apple or Amazon and wondered how exactly people buy a piece of them? You are not alone if the concept of the stock market feels like an exclusive club full of complex charts and jargon. This guide breaks down exactly what a stock is and how you can participate in the financial markets with clarity and confidence.</p>\n<div style=\"text-align:center; margin:28px 0;\"><img src=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/dkte43i3h/image/upload/v1777210097/o9xokuyvinznnmi9gir2.webp\" alt=\"What Is a Stock and How Does It Actually Work\" style=\"max-width:100%; height:auto; border-radius:10px; box-shadow:0 4px 14px rgba(0,0,0,0.13);\"></div><h2 style=\"margin-top:32px; margin-bottom:14px; font-size:1.3em; color:#1a1a1a;\">What Is a Stock and How Does It Actually Work</h2>\n\n<div style=\"overflow-x:auto; -webkit-overflow-scrolling:touch; margin:24px 0; border-radius:6px; box-shadow:0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.08);\"><table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; border-left:none !important; border-right:none !important; border-top:1px solid #d0d0d0; border-bottom:1px solid #d0d0d0; outline:none !important; margin:24px 0; font-size:0.93em; table-layout:auto;\"><thead><tr style=\"background-color:#1565C0;\"><th style=\"padding:11px 14px; border-top:1px solid #d0d0d0; border-bottom:2px solid #1565C0; border-right:1px solid #5090d3; border-left:none !important; text-align:left; font-weight:bold; background-color:#1565C0; color:#ffffff; white-space:nowrap;\">Brokerage Firm</th><th style=\"padding:11px 14px; border-top:1px solid #d0d0d0; border-bottom:2px solid #1565C0; border-right:1px solid #5090d3; border-left:none !important; text-align:left; font-weight:bold; background-color:#1565C0; color:#ffffff; white-space:nowrap;\">Account Minimum</th><th style=\"padding:11px 14px; border-top:1px solid #d0d0d0; border-bottom:2px solid #1565C0; border-right:1px solid #5090d3; border-left:none !important; text-align:left; font-weight:bold; background-color:#1565C0; color:#ffffff; white-space:nowrap;\">Stock Commissions</th><th style=\"padding:11px 14px; border-top:1px solid #d0d0d0; border-bottom:2px solid #1565C0; border-right:1px solid #5090d3; border-left:none !important; text-align:left; font-weight:bold; background-color:#1565C0; color:#ffffff; white-space:nowrap;\">Research Tools</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><td style=\"padding:10px 14px; border-top:1px solid #e8e8e8; border-bottom:1px solid #e8e8e8; border-right:1px solid #e8e8e8; border-left:none !important; vertical-align:top; line-height:1.65; color:#333333;\">Fidelity</td><td style=\"padding:10px 14px; border-top:1px solid #e8e8e8; border-bottom:1px solid #e8e8e8; border-right:1px solid #e8e8e8; border-left:none !important; vertical-align:top; line-height:1.65; color:#333333;\">$0</td><td style=\"padding:10px 14px; border-top:1px solid #e8e8e8; border-bottom:1px solid #e8e8e8; border-right:1px solid #e8e8e8; border-left:none !important; vertical-align:top; line-height:1.65; color:#333333;\">$0</td><td style=\"padding:10px 14px; border-top:1px solid #e8e8e8; border-bottom:1px solid #e8e8e8; border-right:1px solid #e8e8e8; border-left:none !important; vertical-align:top; line-height:1.65; color:#333333;\">Comprehensive</td></tr><tr style=\"background-color:#f5f8ff;\"><td style=\"padding:10px 14px; border-top:1px solid #e8e8e8; border-bottom:1px solid #e8e8e8; border-right:1px solid #e8e8e8; border-left:none !important; vertical-align:top; line-height:1.65; color:#333333;\">Charles Schwab</td><td style=\"padding:10px 14px; border-top:1px solid #e8e8e8; border-bottom:1px solid #e8e8e8; border-right:1px solid #e8e8e8; border-left:none !important; vertical-align:top; line-height:1.65; color:#333333;\">$0</td><td style=\"padding:10px 14px; border-top:1px solid #e8e8e8; border-bottom:1px solid #e8e8e8; border-right:1px solid #e8e8e8; border-left:none !important; vertical-align:top; line-height:1.65; color:#333333;\">$0</td><td style=\"padding:10px 14px; border-top:1px solid #e8e8e8; border-bottom:1px solid #e8e8e8; border-right:1px solid #e8e8e8; border-left:none !important; vertical-align:top; line-height:1.65; color:#333333;\">Advanced</td></tr><tr style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><td style=\"padding:10px 14px; border-top:1px solid #e8e8e8; border-bottom:1px solid #e8e8e8; border-right:1px solid #e8e8e8; border-left:none !important; vertical-align:top; line-height:1.65; color:#333333;\">Robinhood</td><td style=\"padding:10px 14px; border-top:1px solid #e8e8e8; border-bottom:1px solid #e8e8e8; border-right:1px solid #e8e8e8; border-left:none !important; vertical-align:top; line-height:1.65; color:#333333;\">$0</td><td style=\"padding:10px 14px; border-top:1px solid #e8e8e8; border-bottom:1px solid #e8e8e8; border-right:1px solid #e8e8e8; border-left:none !important; vertical-align:top; line-height:1.65; color:#333333;\">$0</td><td style=\"padding:10px 14px; border-top:1px solid #e8e8e8; border-bottom:1px solid #e8e8e8; border-right:1px solid #e8e8e8; border-left:none !important; vertical-align:top; line-height:1.65; color:#333333;\">Basic</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<h2 style=\"margin-top:32px; margin-bottom:14px; font-size:1.3em; color:#1a1a1a;\">Navigating Market Volatility and Risk Management</h2>\n\n<div style=\"text-align:center; margin:28px 0;\"><img src=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/dkte43i3h/image/upload/v1777210098/qi86gffkj8kkwmwvmtxk.webp\" alt=\"Navigating Market Volatility and Risk Management\" style=\"max-width:100%; height:auto; border-radius:10px; box-shadow:0 4px 14px rgba(0,0,0,0.13);\"></div><div style=\"background:#fff8e1; border-left:5px solid #F9A825; padding:18px 22px; margin:32px 0; border-radius:8px;\"><p style=\"margin:0 0 10px 0; font-weight:bold; color:#E65100;\">💡 Expert Tip</p><p style=\"margin:0; line-height:1.8; color:#333;\">As of 2026, many major brokerages offer fractional shares, allowing you to invest in companies with as little as $1. Use these small increments to build a diversified portfolio without needing large amounts of upfront cash.</p></div><div style=\"background:#fff3e0; border-left:5px solid #e53935; padding:18px 22px; margin:32px 0; border-radius:8px;\"><p style=\"margin:0 0 10px 0; font-weight:bold; color:#c62828;\">⚠️ Warning</p><p style=\"margin:0; line-height:1.8; color:#333;\">Be aware that past performance does not guarantee future results in the market. Avoid \"day trading\" or speculative stocks if your primary goal is long-term stability, as these can lead to capital loss exceeding 50% in short durations.</p></div><h2 style=\"margin-top:36px; margin-bottom:16px; font-size:1.25em; color:#1a1a1a;\">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>\n<div style=\"background:#f9f9f9; border:1px solid #e0e0e0; padding:16px 20px; margin:14px 0; border-radius:8px;\"><p style=\"margin:0 0 8px 0; font-weight:bold; color:#1565C0;\">Q. Do I need thousands of dollars to start buying stock?</p><p style=\"margin:0; line-height:1.8; color:#444;\">A. No, as of 2026, many brokerage platforms allow you to start with as little as $1. Fractional share trading has made it possible to own portions of high-value stocks regardless of your initial capital.</p></div>\n<div style=\"background:#f9f9f9; border:1px solid #e0e0e0; padding:16px 20px; margin:14px 0; border-radius:8px;\"><p style=\"margin:0 0 8px 0; font-weight:bold; color:#1565C0;\">Q. What is the difference between a stock and a bond?</p><p style=\"margin:0; line-height:1.8; color:#444;\">A. A stock represents ownership in a company, while a bond is effectively a loan you provide to an entity like a corporation or government. Bonds typically offer fixed interest payments, whereas stocks have no guaranteed payout and higher risk profiles.</p></div>\n<div style=\"background:#f9f9f9; border:1px solid #e0e0e0; padding:16px 20px; margin:14px 0; border-radius:8px;\"><p style=\"margin:0 0 8px 0; font-weight:bold; color:#1565C0;\">Q. How does the stock market affect my taxes?</p><p style=\"margin:0; line-height:1.8; color:#444;\">A. You generally owe capital gains tax when you sell a stock for more than you paid for it. As of 2026, consult with a tax professional regarding your specific bracket, as holding periods longer than one year often qualify for lower long-term capital gains tax rates.</p></div>\n<p style=\"margin:24px 0 8px 0; font-size:0.85em; color:#888; border-top:1px solid #e0e0e0; padding-top:14px;\">※ This content is based on 2026 data and may change with policy or market updates.</p>\n<div style=\"text-align:center; margin:28px 0;\"><img src=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/dkte43i3h/image/upload/v1777210100/bjgfmqws9f9tdd3citlc.webp\" alt=\"마무리 이미지\" style=\"max-width:100%; height:auto; border-radius:10px; box-shadow:0 4px 14px rgba(0,0,0,0.13);\"></div><p>Understanding the mechanics of the stock market provides the foundation for building long-term financial security.</p>\n<p>Of everything covered here, consistent, automated investing matters most.</p>\n<p>Start by opening a brokerage account and setting your first automatic transfer today.</p>\n"
}